# Core reference documents — mandatory upkeep

AbilityAPP maintains **canonical reference docs** in `docs/core/`. Treat them like code: update in the **same slice** as the behaviour they describe.

## Documents

| File | Update when |
|------|-------------|
| [docs/core/SYSTEM-FUNCTION-GUIDE.md](../../docs/core/SYSTEM-FUNCTION-GUIDE.md) | User-visible **function**, outcome, or build status changes |
| [docs/core/WINDOWS-AND-TABS.md](../../docs/core/WINDOWS-AND-TABS.md) | **Window**, **tab**, **route**, sidebar, or process placement changes |
| [docs/core/PROCESSES-AND-WORKFLOWS.md](../../docs/core/PROCESSES-AND-WORKFLOWS.md) | **Process** added/changed, workflow steps, save validation, send/print side effects |
| [docs/core/ENTITY-AND-DATA-MODEL.md](../../docs/core/ENTITY-AND-DATA-MODEL.md) | **FK/child table**, line collection, entity link, reverse nav, compliance-on-save rules |
| [docs/core/ROLES-AND-ACCESS.md](../../docs/core/ROLES-AND-ACCESS.md) | **Role**, default grant, persona, or function-area access changes |
| [docs/core/README.md](../../docs/core/README.md) | New core doc added or source-of-truth paths change |

Read [docs/core/README.md](../../docs/core/README.md) for the index.

## Code triggers (must update WINDOWS-AND-TABS)

| You change | Update WINDOWS-AND-TABS |
|------------|-------------------------|
| `web/src/lib/access/catalog.ts` | Window keys, routes, sidebar, processes |
| `web/src/lib/access/detail-windows.ts` | Tab → window key mapping |
| `web/src/lib/client.ts` (`clientTabGroups`, `clientTabs`) | Client tabs section |
| `web/src/lib/employee.ts` (`employeeTabGroups`) | Employee tabs section |
| `web/src/lib/enquiry.ts`, `incident.ts`, `location.ts` tabs | Matching record tab tables |
| `web/src/lib/system/nav.ts` | System setup section |
| New `AppShell` module or record tab UI | Matching function section |

## Code triggers (must update SYSTEM-FUNCTION-GUIDE)

| You change | Update SYSTEM-FUNCTION-GUIDE |
|------------|------------------------------|
| New module or major workflow | New row in the matching § function table |
| Feature reaches Live / Partial / Planned | Status column |
| Send/print/document behaviour | §18 Documents + affected module § |
| Integration or explicit non-goal | §21 Integrations |

